CHECK:SPACING: spaces preferred around that '+' (ctx:VxV)
#66: FILE: drivers/char/esp.c:181:
+	outb(value, info->io_port+offset);
 	                         ^

Whitespace style used in the kernel sources is described in kernel docs.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

CHECK:UNNECESSARY_PARENTHESES: Unnecessary parentheses around 'info->xmit_cnt <= 0'
#200: FILE: drivers/char/esp.c:664:
+		if ((info->xmit_cnt <= 0) || info->port.tty->stopped) {

Parentheses are not required in the following cases:

  1. Function pointer uses::

      (foo->bar)();

    could be::

      foo->bar();

  2. Comparisons in if::

      if ((foo->bar) && (foo->baz))
      if ((foo == bar))

    could be::

      if (foo->bar && foo->baz)
      if (foo == bar)

  3. addressof/dereference single Lvalues::

      &(foo->bar)
      *(foo->bar)

    could be::

      &foo->bar
      *foo->bar

WARNING:DEEP_INDENTATION: Too many leading tabs - consider code refactoring
#465: FILE: drivers/char/esp.c:1444:
+						if (current_async->port.count > 1)

Indentation with 6 or more tabs usually indicate overly indented
code.

It is suggested to refactor excessive indentation of
if/else/for/do/while/switch statements.

See: https://lore.kernel.org/lkml/1328311239.21255.24.camel@joe2Laptop/

